                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In a letter of December 8, 1948, to General <persName corresp="#p_KGAP1"
                        >Koenig</persName>, not printed, General <persName corresp="#p_CGLD1"
                        >Clay</persName> and General <persName corresp="#p_RSBH1"
                        >Robertson</persName> confirmed that arrangements had been made for the
                    entrance of representatives of the French Military Government into the Combined
                    Coal Control Group. The letter explained that the senior French representative
                    would become a member of the Board of the Coal Control Group with full voting
                    rights. Pending the full fusion of the French Zone with the Bizone, however, the
                    chairmanship of the Board would continue to alternate between the U.S. and U.K.
                    members. This letter was discussed by the Three Western Military Governors at
                    their meeting in Frankfurt on December 16, 1948; regarding that discussion, see
                    the extract from General <persName corresp="#p_CGLD1">Clay’s</persName> message
                    CC–7108, December 18, from Berlin, <ref target="#pg_572">page 572</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
